parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil drops or puddles under the vehicle
oil spraying over the engine
oil pooling around the base of the engine and spark plugs
oil leak noticed when applying brakes
extending stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, engine damage, and loss of engine performance, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Sealant on the #1 plug
oil leak
engine stalling
loss of engine power
difficulty maintaining speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause engine stalling, loss of engine power, and difficulty maintaining speed, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
fuel gauge sending unit failure
difficulty maintaining speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and failure of the subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. The failure of this critical structural component can also lead to costly repairs and compromise the overall safety and reliability of the vehicle.
symptoms: The subframe rusts and cracks
causing the passenger front tire to push back against the fender
leading to loss of control
tire lock-up
and accidents. The vehicle may pull to one side
produce a rubbing noise
and exhibit signs of frame damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front suspension crossmember can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potentially fatal injuries, not only to the driver but also to other drivers on the road.
symptoms: The front suspension crossmember shows signs of rust-through and cracking
particularly in the area of the lower control arm attachment brackets
causing the wheel to become unstable and severely out of alignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The constant squealing of the brakes can be a sign of worn-out brake pads or rotors, which can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes constantly squeal
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, especially when traveling at low speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle does not stop or slows down when the brakes are applied
the rear brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.
